b) Common functions

# function to generate cross-tabulation
crosstab <- function(df,scroll=TRUE,...) {
  
  # anything specified after df will be treated as a var
  args <- quos(...) 
  
  d<- df %>%
    # keep only vars specified
    select(!!!args) %>%  
    # group by all combinations of variables
    group_by(!!!args) %>%
    # calculate n and percentages for each category
    mutate(N   = prettyNum(n(),big.mark=","),
           Pct = round((n() / nrow(.))*100,2)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    distinct() %>%
    verify(anyDuplicated(select(.,c(!!!args))) == 0) %>%
    arrange(!!!args) %>%  
    # add table formatting 
    kbl(full_width = T, 
        align = "l") %>%
    kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped","hover"))
  
  if (scroll == TRUE) { d %>% scroll_box(width = "100%", height = "600px") }
  else { d }
  
}

The goal of this project is to estimate the impact of schooling on earnings based on the introduction of compulsory schooling. Suppose that you are looking at a setting in which there was no compulsory schooling for individuals born prior to September 1, 1951, but for individuals born after September 1, 1951, a minimum school leaving age was introduced and set to age 16.

Please download final_data_1.csv. This dataset contains the following individual-level data (each row in the dataset corresponds to an individual):

  • birthyear: individual’s year of birth (1947-1955)

  • birthmonth: individual’s month of birth (1-12)

  • birthday: individual’s day of birth (1-31)

  • lnearn45: individual’s earnings measured at age 45

  • married45: individual’s marital status measured at age 45

  • haskids45: individual’s presence of children measured at age 45

  • s: individual’s years of schooling completed

  • min_schl_age: the minimum school leaving age that applied to the individual

1) Import & validate data

# load RD data set
rd_dta <- read_csv("final_data_1.csv") %>%
          # confirm number of observations = 201,279
          verify(nrow(.) == 201279) %>%
          # confirm 8 variables
          verify(ncol(.) == 8) %>%
          # confirm identity of 8 variables
          verify(colnames(.) %in% c("min_schl_age","s","birthyear","birthday",
                                    "birthmonth","lnearn45","married45","haskids45")) %>%
          # check values of each variable
          verify(min_schl_age %in% c(0,16)) %>%
          verify(s %in% c(9,10,11,12,14,16,18)) %>%
          verify(birthyear %in% c(1947,1948,1949,1950,1951,1952,1953,1954,1955)) %>%
          verify(dplyr::between(birthday,1,31)) %>%
          verify(dplyr::between(birthmonth,1,12)) %>%
          verify(dplyr::between(lnearn45,9.38,13.39)) %>%
          verify(married45 %in% c(0,1)) %>%
          verify(haskids45 %in% c(0,1))

X: Whether student left school at or after age 16

Y: Earnings, marital status, having children

Z: Minimum school age requirement (i.e., was born on or after September 1, 1951).

First stage: X ~ Z

Second stage: Y ~ X_hat

Inclusion condition: The instrument (minimum school age requirement) is a strong predictor of years of schooling (X). I.e., ideally t-statistic for the coefficient on Z in first-stage equation has an absolute value of 3 or higher.

Exclusion condition: Minimum school age policy must not directly affect earnings/marital status/parental status (i.e., dependent variables Y); the only effect minimum age policy should have on earnings/marital status/parental status is via the pathway through X (number of years of schooling). That is, minimum school leaving age policy must not be correlated with any factor in the error term in the second-stage equation (i.e., when Y is regressed on X and the other covariates).

9) First stage plots

Plot whether student was born on or after September 1, 1951 (i.e., treated) against running variable (birthdate relative to policy taking effect)

plot_fs <- function(df,
                    sharp = TRUE,
                    binned_run_var,
                    treat_var,
                    xlab,
                    ylab) {
  
  if (sharp == TRUE) { type <- "Sharp" }
  else               { type <- "Fuzzy" }
  
  plot_dta <- df %>%
              group_by(!!sym(binned_run_var)) %>%
              summarise(mean_treat = mean(!!sym(treat_var)) * 100)
  
  ggplot(plot_dta, aes(x = !!sym(binned_run_var), y = mean_treat)) +
         # add connecting line
         geom_line(color='red', size=1.5) +
         # add data points
         geom_point(size = 3, color = "dodgerblue") +
         expand_limits(y = 0) +
         # add labels
         labs(y = ylab,   
              x = xlab) +
         geom_vline(xintercept = 0, lty=2) +
         # add title
         ggtitle(paste0("First stage: ",type," RD")) + 
         # add formatting
         theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
               panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
               panel.background = element_blank(), 
               axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
               plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 14))
  
  
}

# Sharp RD
plot_fs(df = rd_dta,
        sharp = TRUE,
        binned_run_var = "runvarbin_90day",
        treat_var = "subject_to_policy",
        xlab = "Student birthdate relative to September 1, 1951 (90-day bins)",
        ylab = "Percent subject to minimum school \n drop-out age policy")

# Fuzzy RD
plot_fs(df = rd_dta,
        sharp = FALSE,
        binned_run_var = "runvarbin_90day",
        treat_var = "left_sch_age16_or_later",
        xlab = "Student birthdate relative to September 1, 1951 (90-day bins)",
        ylab = "Percent left school at \n age 16+")

10) First-stage permutation test

stopifnot(min(rd_dta$runvar) == -1704)
stopifnot(max(rd_dta$runvar) == 1582)

plot_permutation_test_fs <- function(df,
                                     x_var,
                                     z_var,
                                     run_var,
                                     n_simulations) {
  
  # run real first stage regression
  rdfs_lm = lm(get(x_var) ~ get(run_var) + get(z_var) + I(get(z_var) * get(run_var)), data = df)

  # store estimate on z
  z_est_fs = coefficients(rdfs_lm)[3]
  
  # initialize empty data frame for first stage results
  coefs <- tibble(estimate_fs = numeric())
  
  plot_dta <- df %>%
              mutate(x = get(x_var))
  
  for(ii in 1:n_simulations) {
    
    # randomly assign distance relative to policy start date and use this to reconstruct instrument (whether student is subject to policy)
    plot_dta %<>% 
      mutate(new_runvar = sample(-1704:1582,nrow(.),replace=TRUE)) %>%
      mutate(had_policy = ifelse(new_runvar >= 0,1,0))
    
    # run first stage with random instrument
    reg_fs = lm(x ~ new_runvar + had_policy + I(had_policy * new_runvar), data = plot_dta)
    
    # store estimates on Z
    coefs <- coefs %>%
             add_row(estimate_fs = coefficients(reg_fs)['had_policy'])
  
  }
  
  # plot first-stage permutation test results
  ggplot(coefs, mapping = aes(estimate_fs)) +
    geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'dodgerblue') +
    labs(y = "Number of simulations",   
         x = "Estimated coefficient on simulated treatment assignment") +
    # plot true estimate
    geom_vline(xintercept = z_est_fs, lty=2, size = 1.5, color = 'red') +
         # add title
         ggtitle(paste0("First-stage permuation test")) + 
         # add formatting
         theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
               panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
               panel.background = element_blank(), 
               axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
               plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 14))
   
}

# FS permutation test
plot_permutation_test_fs(df = rd_dta,
                         x_var = "left_sch_age16_or_later",
                         z_var = "subject_to_policy",
                         run_var = "runvar",
                         n_simulations = 500)

plot_frequencies <- function(df,
                             binned_run_var,
                             xlab,
                             bin_size) {

  plot_dta <- df %>%
              group_by(!!sym(binned_run_var)) %>%
              summarise(n = n())
  
  ggplot(plot_dta, aes(x = !!sym(binned_run_var), y = n)) +
         # add connecting line
         geom_line(color='red', size=1.5) +
         expand_limits(y = 0) +
         # add data points
         geom_point(size = 3, color = "dodgerblue") +
         # add labels
         labs(y = "Number of students in bin",   
              x = xlab) +
         geom_vline(xintercept = 0, lty=2) +
         # add title
         ggtitle(paste0("Frequencies plot: Bin size = ",bin_size," days")) + 
         # add formatting
         theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
               panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
               panel.background = element_blank(), 
               axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
               plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 14))
  
  
}

13) Reduced form plots

plot_rf <- function(df,
                    binned_run_var,
                    y_var,
                    xlab,
                    ylab,
                    ymin,
                    ymax) {
  
  plot_dta <- df %>%
              group_by(!!sym(binned_run_var)) %>%
              summarise(mean_y = mean(!!sym(y_var)))
  
  if (y_var %in% c("married45","haskids45")) {plot_dta %<>% mutate(mean_y = mean_y * 100)}
  
  ggplot(plot_dta, aes(x = !!sym(binned_run_var), y = mean_y)) +
         # add connecting line
         geom_line(color='red', size=1.5) +
         # add data points
         geom_point(size = 3, color = "dodgerblue") +
         # add labels
         labs(y = ylab,   
              x = xlab) +
         #expand_limits(y = 0) +
         scale_y_continuous(limits = c(ymin, ymax)) +
         geom_vline(xintercept = 0, lty=2) +
         # add title
         ggtitle(paste0("Reduced form: ",ylab)) + 
         # add formatting
         theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
               panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
               panel.background = element_blank(), 
               axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
               plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 14))
  
  
}

14) Reduced form permutation test

plot_permutation_test_rf <- function(df,
                                     y_var,
                                     z_var,
                                     run_var,
                                     y_var_text,
                                     n_simulations) {
  
  # run real reduced form regression
  rdrf_lm = lm(get(y_var) ~ get(run_var) + get(z_var) + I(get(z_var) * get(run_var)), data = df)
  
  # store estimate on z
  z_est_rf = coefficients(rdrf_lm)[3]
  
  # initialize empty data frame for first stage and reduced form permutation test results
  coefs <- tibble(estimate_rf = numeric())
  
  plot_dta <- df %>%
              mutate(y = get(y_var))
  
  for(ii in 1:n_simulations) {
    
    # randomly assign distance relative to policy start date and use this to reconstruct instrument (whether student is subject to policy)
    plot_dta %<>% 
      mutate(new_runvar = sample(-1704:1582,nrow(.),replace=TRUE)) %>%
      mutate(had_policy = ifelse(new_runvar >= 0,1,0))

    # run reduced form with random instrument
    reg_rf = lm(y ~ new_runvar + had_policy + I(had_policy * new_runvar), data = plot_dta)
    
    # store estimates on Z
    coefs <- coefs %>%
             add_row(estimate_rf = coefficients(reg_rf)['had_policy'])
  
  }
  
  # plot reduced form permutation test results
  ggplot(coefs, mapping = aes(estimate_rf)) +
    geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'dodgerblue') +
    labs(y = "Number of simulations",   
         x = "Estimated coefficient on simulated treatment assignment") +
    # plot true estimate
    geom_vline(xintercept = z_est_rf, lty=2,color='red',size=1.5) +
         # add title
         ggtitle(paste0("Reduced form permuation test (outcome = ",y_var_text,")")) + 
         # add formatting
         theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
               panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
               panel.background = element_blank(), 
               axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
               plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 14))
   
}

Earnings

plot_permutation_test_rf(df = rd_dta,
                      y_var = "lnearn45",
                      z_var = "subject_to_policy",
                      run_var = "runvar",
                      y_var_text = "average \n earnings at age 45 (logged)",
                      n_simulations = 500)
